org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.rmnode

Interface RMNode

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<RMNode>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRMNode, RMDeployingNode, RMNodeImpl

    public interface RMNode
extends Comparable<RMNode>
    An RMNode is a ProActive node able to execute schedulers tasks. So an RMNode is a representation of a ProActive node object with its associated NodeSource, and its state in the Resource Manager :
    -free : node is ready to perform a task.
    -busy : node is executing a task.
    -to be released : node is busy and have to be removed at the end of the its current task.
    -down : node is broken, and not anymore able to perform tasks.

    Resource Manager can select nodes that verify criteria. this selection is implemented with SelectionScript objects. Each node memorize results of executed scripts, in order to answer faster to a selection already asked.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
    NodeSource, SelectionScript
